                  </persName>
            . I live at Bull Cross. My little girl was sent on an errand with her bonnet  on on the 16th of August, about four o'clock, and she came home without it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-239-person1998">
                  PHILLIS 
                  BALAAM
               <interp inst="t18240916-239-person1998" type="surname" value="BALAAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-239-person1998" type="given" value="PHILLIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-239-person1998" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am thirteen years of age. On Saturday, the 16th of August, I was playing in a barn with some children, and pulled off my bonnet, and hung it on a nail in the barn: I went on Sunday night to look for it, and it was gone; I was going on an errand on Monday morning, and met a woman with it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-239-person1999">
                  JAMES 
                  CLARKS
               <interp inst="t18240916-239-person1999" type="surname" value="CLARKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-239-person1999" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-239-person1999" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Mr. Cole's, Bull Cross. This little girl lives servant there; my master sent me after this man, when she said she had lost her bonnet; I pursued him three miles, and found him with a bonnet and a gown; he said he had bought the bonnet, and he would not deliver it up till he had found the man he bought it of, who lived at Mr. Bottomly's. This was about nine o'clock on Monday morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-239-person2000">
                  JOHN 
                  MEAD
               <interp inst="t18240916-239-person2000" type="surname" value="MEAD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-239-person2000" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-239-person2000" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I apprehended the prisoner. The bonnet was given by me to Clarke before the Magistrates.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man came up to me as I was going to Waltham Abbey; he goes by the name of Baker or 
               <persName id="t18240916-239-person2001">
                  John 
                  Russel
               <interp inst="t18240916-239-person2001" type="surname" value="Russel"></interp>
